{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>All functionally characterised members of the ammonium transporter family are ammonia or ammonium uptake transporters. Some, but not others, also transport methylammonium. Uptake of ammonium/ammonia by AtmB protein from E. coli is electrogenic. Following sequestration of NH4+ at the periplasmic face, NH4+ is deprotonated and neutral NH3 is transported into the cytoplasm. Neutral NH3 and charged H+ are carried separately across the membrane on a unique two-lane pathway, before recombining to NH4+ inside the cell. It also acts as a sensor of the extracellular ammonium concentration [[cite:PUB00097856], [cite:PUB00097855]].</p>\n\n<p>This entry represents ammonium transporters belonging to the Amt family, but it does not include the Rhesus (Rh) subgroup.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "1u7g", "name" "Crystal Structure of Ammonia Channel AmtB from E. Coli"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR029020", "name" "Ammonium/urea transporter", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR43029" "AMMONIUM TRANSPORTER MEP2"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR00836" "ammonium transporter"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Ammonium transporter", "short" "Ammonium_transpt"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 38, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 9126, "taxa" 34060, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 55056, "sets" 0, "proteins" 55007, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 40524}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"prositedoc" {"displayName" "PROSITE Doc", "description" "PROSITE is a database of protein families and domains.", "rank" 18, "accessions" [{"accession" "PDOC00937", "url" "http://prosite.expasy.org/PDOC00937"}]}}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR001905", :literature {"PUB00097855" {"URL" nil, "issue" nil, "authors" ["Williamson G" "Tamburrino G" "Bizior A" "Boecks